info.title: Fuel API
info.description: The Fuel API has been developed as a means of accessing live pricing across all current Australian service stations. It is advised that you read the contents of this documentation carefully which includes restrictions and responsibilities that would be necessary to allow appropriate interaction with the API. The v1 API can only access data for NSW. The v2 API includes data for Tasmania (TAS) as well as NSW.

get.description: The client can request an access token using only its client credentials (or other supported means of authentication) when the client is requesting access to the protected resources under its control, or those of another resource owner that have been previously arranged with the authorization server.

parameters.description: Base64 encoded value of api_key:api_secret. Eg 'Basic {Base64 encoded value of api_key:api_secret}'

get.description: Returns lists of reference data to be used in subsequent requests. It is recommended to execute this call in a separate api client as response can be over 2 mb. This API returns data for NSW.

parameters.name: Authorization
parameters.description: 'Bearer {token}', where {token} is the value obtained from accesstoken call under security.

parameters.name: Content-Type
parameters.description: Content-Type should be 'application/json; charset=utf-8'

parameters.name: apikey
parameters.description: Api key value obtained from your approved app.

parameters.name: transactionid
parameters.description: Unique ID of this call

parameters.name: requesttimestamp
parameters.description: UTC date and time of request. Format dd/MM/yyyy hh:mm:ss AM/PM

parameters.description: The state that the station is in (as stationCode is not guaranteed to be unique across states), e.g. 'NSW' or 'TAS'. Omitting this argument (or leaving it empty) will default the state to 'NSW'.
